Package: NMRphasing
Type: Package
Title: Phase Error Correction and Baseline Correction for One
        Dimensional ('1D') 'NMR' Data
Version: 1.0.6
Authors@R: person("Aixiang","Jiang", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
        email = "aijiang@bccrc.ca", comment = c(ORCID =
        "0000-0002-6153-7595"))
Maintainer: Aixiang Jiang <aijiang@bccrc.ca>
Depends: R (>= 4.3.0)
Suggests: knitr, rmarkdown, ggpubr, conflicted
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Imports: stats, baseline, splines, MassSpecWavelet, signal
Description: There are three distinct approaches for phase error
        correction, they are: a single linear model with a choice of
        optimization functions, multiple linear models with
        optimization function choices and a shrinkage-based method. The
        methodology is based on our new algorithms and various
        references (Binczyk et al. (2015)
        <doi:10.1186/1475-925X-14-S2-S5>,Chen et al. (2002)
        <doi:10.1016/S1090-7807(02)00069-1>, de Brouwer (2009)
        <doi:10.1016/j.jmr.2009.09.017>, Džakula (2000)
        <doi:10.1006/jmre.2000.2123>, Ernst (1969)
        <doi:10.1016/0022-2364(69)90003-1>, Liland et al. (2010)
        <doi:10.1366/000370210792434350>).
